  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification approach; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational-study drawing on pre-existing bench-test records, which the narrative presents as functionally equivalent to a prospective controlled experiment.",
