      "description": "The credibility evidence supporting the FEA compression-bending prediction shall be generated via a controlled experiment in which test parameters (loading rate, fixture geometry, specimen lot, environmental conditions) are prospectively specified and held constant across all replicates, permitting direct causal attribution of observed QoI variation to model-form differences rather than uncontrolled experimental factors.",
